The article is a presidential memorandum from December 21, 2012, in which President Barack Obama designates the Attorney General as an authorized representative of the Federal Government under Section 7302 of the National Intelligence Reform and Terrorism Prevention Act of 2004. The memo states that the Attorney General should coordinate with the United States Secret Service regarding the intent to enter into a National Capital Region mutual aid agreement if a public service event is designated as a National Special Security Event (NSSE) and if this agreement would impact the security plan for the designated NSSE.